def regressionGroups(df,by, x_var1,x_var2, y_var):
    group = df[by].unique()
    rsquared, betas_, shape,rsquared1,betas_1 = [],[],[],[],[]
    xr1 = x_var1+'_r'
    xr2 = x_var2+'_r'
    xbeta1 = x_var1+'_beta'
    xbeta2 = x_var2+'_beta'

    for i in group:
        df_asset = df[df[by] == i]
        shape.append(df_asset.shape[0])
        x = np.asarray(df_asset[x_var1]).reshape(-1,1)
        y = np.asarray(df_asset[y_var]) 
        model = LinearRegression().fit(x,y)
        rsquared.append(model.score(x,y))
        betas_.append(model.coef_[0])

    r = np.asarray(rsquared)
    b = np.asarray(betas_)
    s = np.asarray(shape)

    results = pd.DataFrame({by:group, xr1:r, xbeta1:b, '# of Data Points':s})

    for j in group:
        df_asset1 = df[df[by] == j]
        x1 = np.asarray(df_asset1[x_var2]).reshape(-1,1)
        y1 = np.asarray(df_asset1[y_var]) 
        model1 = LinearRegression().fit(x1,y1)
        rsquared1.append(model1.score(x1,y1))
        betas_1.append(model1.coef_[0])

    r1 = np.asarray(rsquared1)
    b1 = np.asarray(betas_1)

    results[xr2] = r1
    results[xbeta2] = b1

    results.dropna(inplace=True)

    print('#'*15,f' {x_var1} ','#'*15)
    print(f'Median R-Squared: {np.median(results[xr1]):.2%}')
    print(f'Median Beta values: {round(np.median(results[xbeta1]),4)}')
    print('#'*15,f' {x_var2} ','#'*15)
    print(f'Median R-Squared: {np.median(results[xr2]):.2%}')
    print(f'Median Beta values: {round(np.median(results[xbeta2]),4)}')

    plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))
    sns.histplot(data=results,x=xr1,color = 'skyblue',label = x_var1, kde = True, binwidth = .05)
    sns.histplot(data=results,x=xr2,color = 'green',label =x_var2, kde = True, binwidth = .05)
    plt.legend(loc=1, prop={'size': 15})
    plt.xlabel('R-Squared')
    plt.show()

    return results

def evaluate(actual,pred):
    pred = np.asarray(pred)
    actual = np.asarray(actual)

    mape = np.mean(np.abs((pred - actual) / np.abs(actual)))
    corr = np.corrcoef(pred, actual)[0,1]
    rmse = np.sqrt(np.mean((pred - actual) ** 2))

    print(f'MAPE: {round(mape,4)}')
    print(f'Correlation: {round(corr,4)}')
    print(f'RMSE: {round(rmse,4)}')

msa = df['MSA'].unique()
durbMig, durbJob = [],[]
for market in msa:
    dftmp = df[df['MSA'] == market]
    x = dftmp['Net Migration']
    y = dftmp['Rent Growth']
    modeltmp = ols('Q("Rent Growth") ~ Q("Net Migration")', data=dftmp).fit()
    durbMig.append(durbin_watson(modeltmp.resid))

    x1 = dftmp['Job Growth']
    y1 = dftmp['Rent Growth']
    modeltmp1 = ols('Q("Rent Growth") ~ Q("Job Growth")', data=dftmp).fit()
    durbJob.append(durbin_watson(modeltmp1.resid))

durbDF = pd.DataFrame({'MSA':msa,'Durbin-Watson Migration':durbMig,'Durbin-Watson Job':durbJob})


print(f'Durbin-Watson Migration: {round(durbDF["Durbin-Watson Migration"].mean(),2)}')

Stationary Test & Dicky- Fuller Test¶

In [ ]:
def dickyFuller(variable, by, Print=False):
    group = df[by].unique()
    adfStat, pvals = [],[]
    
    for i in group:
        res = adfuller(df[df[by] == i][variable])    
        adfStat.append(res[0])
        pvals.append(res[1])
    
    if Print:
        print('#'*10,f'{variable} ran by {by}','#'*10)
        # print(f'Median ADF Stat: {np.median(adfStat)}')
        print(f'Median P-value: {np.median(pvals)}')

    return group, adfStat, pvals
